    "reasoning": "The problem describes a finite state machine (FSM) with specific behavior based on inputs s and w. The FSM starts in state A, transitions to state B when s=1, and then monitors w over three clock cycles. If w=1 in exactly two of those cycles, it sets output z=1 in the next cycle. We'll need to define states for this FSM. Since the FSM needs to track the count of w=1 over 3 cycles, we must use appropriate state encoding. The states can be defined as follows: A (initial state, waiting for s=1), B (waiting for first w sample), C (waiting for second w sample), D (waiting for third w sample). We also need to track number of w=1 occurrences in a counter. Using localparam to define these states ensures they are constants. The combinational logic will determine the next state and output based on current state and inputs. Sequential logic updates the state and counter registers on every clock cycle (with reset). The reset signal is synchronous high, so the state gets reset to A upon reset assertion. The implementation avoids using 'inside' or 'unique' keywords, and all signals are declared as 'logic'. A counter tracks w=1 occurrences, and we ensure proper initialization of flip-flops with an initial block if needed.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input reset,\n    input s,\n    input w,\n    output z\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam STATE_A = 2'b00;\n    localparam STATE_B = 2'b01;\n    localparam STATE_C = 2'b10;\n    localparam STATE_D = 2'b11;\n\n    // State and counter variables\n    logic [1:0] state;\n    logic [1:0] state_next;\n    logic [1:0] w_count;\n    logic [1:0] w_count_next;\n    logic z_next;\n\n    // Sequential logic\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset)\n            state <= STATE_A;\n        else\n            state <= state_next;\n\n        if (reset)\n            w_count <= 2'b00;\n        else\n            w_count <= w_count_next;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state and output\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            STATE_A: begin\n                if (s)\n                    state_next = STATE_B;\n                else\n                    state_next = STATE_A;\n                w_count_next = 2'b00;\n                z_next = 1'b0;\n            end\n\n            STATE_B: begin\n                if (w)\n                    w_count_next = 2'b01;\n                else\n                    w_count_next = 2'b00;\n                state_next = STATE_C;\n                z_next = 1'b0;\n            end\n\n            STATE_C: begin\n                if (w)\n                    w_count_next = w_count + 2'b01;\n                else\n                    w_count_next = w_count;\n                state_next = STATE_D;\n                z_next = 1'b0;\n            end\n\n            STATE_D: begin\n                if (w)\n                    w_count_next = w_count + 2'b01;\n                else\n                    w_count_next = w_count;\n                if (w_count_next == 2'b10)\n                    z_next = 1'b1;\n                else\n                    z_next = 1'b0;\n                state_next = STATE_A;\n            end\n\n            default:\n                state_next = STATE_A;\n                w_count_next = 2'b00;\n                z_next = 1'b0;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Assign output\n    assign z = z_next;\n\nendmodule"
}
